Operatives of the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA) have arrested a 27-year-old graduate of Accountancy, from the Bayero University, Kano (BUK), Zakaru Baba, at the Mallam Aminu Kano International Airport, Kano with 6kg of cannabis sativa. The agencyâ€™s spokesman, Femi Babafemi said on Tuesday in a statement that the consignment was flown from Lagos to Kano on Saturday, May 29 via Max Air, Babafemi said. The suspect who turned up to claim the packaged drug was arrested, the statement said. Babafemi said it was the first time the Command has apprehended a suspect via the domestic wing of the airport, as most arrests and seizures are usually made at the international wing. A 23-year-old secondary school leaver, Iwuyi Princewill Chukwuka, was also arrested for allegedly attempting to smuggle 6.3kg of skunk to Turkey, Babafemi said. He was arrested at the Nnamdi Azikiwe International Airport (NAIA), with the illicit drugs concealed in cray fish and stuffed inside Golden Morn packs. Also arrested was a Europe-based Nigerian, Peter Mkwo, 37, for attempting smuggle three kilogrammes of methamphetamine to Belgium.